weather.description: Showers possible.
Showers possible.

Scattered showers and storms of the pop-up variety, winds in the 10-15mph range. To know more about specifics on rain timing/intensity we'll need to do it right before kickoff with some radar analysis, models aren't going to help.
Showers possible.

Looking increasingly likely that the rain (or at least the heavy rain) is clear before kickoff, though some straggler showers could remain. Winds however should still be going pretty good, 15-20mph sustained with stronger gusts, that's a bump down to the passing attack.
Chance of a stray shower or storm, not likely.

I guess I need to start making a note about adding wildfire risk in these west coast games, and SF is certainly at the top of that list. I've heard they will consider a PPD for an AQI over 200, which is certainly in the realm of possibility, hopefully we'll learn more well before the slate kicks off. Note to add that I'm seeing a current AQI of 152, and it has been gradually dropping, so while I'm not certain, I expect things will turn out ok here.
Similar wildfire / smoke concerns.
